y has been to move up a layer of abstraction and reliably engineer new gene=
tic circuits. This type of progress would unlock a future of programmable m=
edicines and materials, where our medicines&#8212;and maybe someday our clo=
thes, buildings, and physical infrastructure&#8212;flexibly adapt and compu=
te based on their environment.</p><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16=
px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">In this recent essay, I explain=
 exciting new research from a synthetic biology lab at Rice University that=
 aims to accelerate genetic circuit design by leveraging recent advances in=
 DNA sequencing. It&#8217;s a great example of the promise at the intersect=
